# Archiver Codebase

## Project structure

```
local/
  run.sh              orchestrator — always use this to start downloads
  stop.sh             graceful shutdown — always use before rebooting
  config/
    registry.yaml     master model list (source of truth)
    drives.yaml       drive mount points and roles
  src/archiver/
    cli.py            click commands: download, verify, status, list, drives, tokens, pin
    downloader.py     per-model download logic (LFS via aria2, XET via hf_hub_download)
    scheduler.py      worker pool; max parallel models + max per drive; add more when speed/(n+1) >= 6 MB/s
    aria2_manager.py  aria2c daemon (16 concurrent files; optional --bandwidth-cap)
    state.py          run_state.json persistence (thread-safe)
    status.py         rich live UI + STATUS.md + RunReport
    models.py         ModelEntry / DriveConfig dataclasses + registry I/O
    verifier.py       SHA-256, manifest.json, global_index.jsonl
    preflight.py      pre-flight checks
```

## Key bugs fixed in this session

- **`models.py` `model_dir`**: falls back to `"main"` when `commit_sha` is None — never returns None if `drive_path` is set
- **`state.py`**: `threading.Lock` protects `run_state.json`; writes via `.json.tmp` → rename
- **`aria2_manager.py`**: `--allow-overwrite=true`; removes orphaned partials (file exists but no `.aria2` control file) before submitting to aria2
- **`downloader.py`**: `GatedRepoError` + HTTP 401/403 raise `AuthError` immediately — no retry
- **`scheduler.py`**: SIGTERM/SIGINT sets `_stop_event`; workers stop cleanly between models
- **`run.sh`**: traps SIGTERM/SIGINT → forwards to Python child; writes `.archiver.pid`

## Design rules

- Downloads are always resumable — never delete `.tmp` partial files or `.aria2` control files
- run_state.json lives on D5; `.tmp` scratch lives on D1 (not D5)
- `commit_sha` in registry.yaml is auto-pinned after first download
- LFS CDN URLs expire ~1 hour — always re-fetch with `hf_hub_url()` before each attempt
- On SHA-256 mismatch: remove both the corrupt file AND its `.aria2` control file (force clean restart)
- `sync_archive()` replicates `archive/` to all drives after each model completes
- Concurrency: MAX_FILES_IN_FLIGHT=8 per model (downloader.py); ARIA2_MAX_CONCURRENT=16 (aria2_manager.py). Bandwidth cap (if set) is applied in aria2 only.

## Adding a model to registry.yaml

```yaml
org/ModelName:
  hf_repo: org/ModelName
  commit_sha: null        # auto-pinned on first download
  tier: A                 # A/B/C/D
  priority: 1             # 1 = no token, 2 = gated (HF_TOKEN + licence acceptance)
  drive: d1
  requires_auth: false
  licence: Apache-2.0
  notes: "description"
```

## HF token

```bash
bash deploy/sethfToken.sh hf_YOURTOKEN   # stores in ~/.hf_token (chmod 600)
uv run archiver tokens check             # verify gated model access
```
